                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                              <td valign="top" style="font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color:#333333; font-size:12px; text-align:justify;">As mentioned earlier, children always seek to be treated as adults. Try to keep  your child informed about your finances and be as honest with your child as  possible. You can also ask your child to join you during a financial plan  review to understand the process better. As a parent, you are responsible in  imparting financial education to your child. Don’t let them commit the same  mistakes you made by not introducing them to the basic of money management at  an early age.</td>
